title: 15 inch MacBook Pro retina (i7, 16gb, 512gb) dual graphics
description:
I'm selling my beloved 15 inch MacBook Pro with retina display, 16 GB of RAM, and 512 GB solid-state hard drive space. 
 
macOS Sierra 
Version 10.12.2 
 
Processor: 2.3 GHz Intel core i7 
Memory: 16 GB 1600 MHz DDR3 
Graphics: Dual 
    -Nvidia GeForce GT 750M 2048 MB 
    -Intel iris Pro 1536 MB 
 
I find it important to understand why someone is selling; below are my reasons: 
 
This is my absolute favorite laptop and was perfect for my first two years of medical school. I am no longer in the classroom and I am constantly on the go. I am unable to fit a 15 inch computer in my whitecoat pocket; as a father, I hardly have an opportunity to 'sit'. I hope to pass on this wonderful device to someone who will appreciate it as much as I do and will benifit from it more than I can.  
 
I proudly say it isn't free of any blemishes as this laptop is too useful to keep in a closet untouched. There is one small indentation in the middle of the right speaker grille, peraps the laptops most vulnerable location to a falling frigerator magnet (couresey of my 2-year old son). The back right external corner also shows wear (multitidue of times entering and exiting my bag). 
 
This is the very last Macbook Pro Retina prior to apple implementing the force touch trackpad. If you are familiar with apple products over the past 10 years, you already notice the absence of Steve Jobs. My Macbook Pro is his last design . My machine has an ethereal charm that is missing on the new force touch models. Perhaps it's sentimental, but see for yourself if you wish.

title: MAGSAFE 2 Macbook Charger
description:
We carry 45W, 60W, and 85W. 
The MagSafe 2 Power Adapter features a magnetic DC connector that ensures your power cable will disconnect if it experiences undue strain and helps prevent fraying or weakening of the cables over time. In addition, the magnetic DC helps guide the plug into the system for a quick and secure connection. 
 
When the connection is secure, an LED located at the head of the DC connector will light; an amber light lets you know that your portable is charging, while a green light tells you that you have a full charge. description:
Apple MacBook Pro "Core i7" 2.5 15" Mid-2014. Comes with box and ac adapter  
 
Apple MacBook Pro Retina 15-Inch Mid-2014The MacBook Pro "Core i7" 2.5 15-Inch (Dual Graphics - Mid-2014 Retina Display) features a 22 nm "Haswell/Crystalwell" 2.5 GHz Intel "Core i7" processor (4870HQ), with four independent processor "cores" on a single silicon chip, a 6 MB shared level 3 cache, 16 GB of onboard 1600 MHz DDR3L SDRAM (which cannot be upgraded later), 512 GB of PCIe-based flash storage, and dual graphics processors -- a NVIDIA GeForce GT 750M with 2 GB of dedicated GDDR5 memory and an integrated Intel Iris 5200 Pro graphics processor with 128 MB of "Crystalwell" embedded DRAM (and shared system memory). It also has an integrated 720p FaceTime HD webcam and a high-resolution LED-backlit 15.4" widescreen 2880x1800 (220 ppi) "Retina" display in a case that weighs just less than 4.5 pounds (2.02 kg). It does not have an internal optical drive. 
 
Connectivity includes 802.11ac Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, two USB 3.0 ports, two "Thunderbolt 2" ports, an HDMI port, an audio in/out port, and an SDXC card slot. 
 
In addition, this model has a backlit keyboard, a "no button" glass "inertial" multi-touch trackpad, a "MagSafe 2" power adapter, and an internal, sealed battery that provides an Apple estimated 8 hours of battery life.

title: Lenovo X1 Carbon Ultrabook Notebook - i7 / 8gb RAM / 256 SSD *EXTRAS*
description:
I write code for a living.   
 
What I am offering for sale is a total computing solution rather than a mere computer.  I bought it as a graduation present to myself for $1200 a couple years ago it was incredibly fast then and even faster now. 
 
The lenovo x1 carbon is pretty much the perfect amount of machine.  It masterfully blends power and performance while not cutting many corners.  Here are the raw specs, they kind of tell most of the story: 
 
Lenovo X1 Carbon, weighs 2 lbs 15 oz (see picture) 
 
Intel i5 2.5ghz multi core processor Hyper-Threading Technology, Intel Turbo Boost Technology 2.0 3mb cache, integrated memory controller 
 
8GB 1333 MHz PC3-10600 Ram 
 
120 GB Solid State Disk Drive 
 
Intel HD Graphics 4000 
 
Full size spill-resistant backlit keyboard 
 
Buttonless touchpad (like a macbook pro) 
 
Bluetooth 4.0, Ethernet, Fast Ethernet, Gigabit Ethernet 
 
Mini DisplayPort, USB 2.0, USB 3.0, headphone/microphone combo jack 
 
Fingerprint Scanner 
 
and all this is encased in a durable and impossibly light carbon fiber, magnesium-aluminum alloy frame. 
 
This machine cost $1500 in 2012 and it's easy to see why. 
 
 
If i had any complaints about this machine then it was merely  too few output ports.  Fret not, I got you covered, remember when I said total computing solution? 
 
So I am including with this machine - A docking station/port replicator that will send outputs to three different displays (that's a lotta desktop) as well as add an additional. 
 
When you plug this dock into the lenovo you will instantly add the following ports to the Carbon X1 
 
2 x USB 3.0 -- 1 provides always-on mobile device charging 
2 x USB 2.0 
1 x DVI-D 
1x Gigabit Ethernet 
1x Stereo/Mic Combo Port 
 
So in other words, you can leave a wireless mouse, wireless keyboard, a larger external display, a printer, and an external DVD drive plugged in to the stationary dock, and when you get home, plug the dock into your carbon and your home office springs to life.   
 
It's a pretty damn cool setup.  My price may seem high, but there's a reason for that.  I've done all the work for you, and am including several accessories.  this is ready to go. 
 
THIS WILL ALSO COME WITH A FULLY ACTIVATED COPY OF MS OFFICE 2016 PROFESSIONAL PLUS & PHOTOSHOP CS6 PREINSTALLED ON THE COMPUTER.   
 
Computer is Mint 
 
I have many other computers and parts for sale, to see the others click 'more ads by this user' to see the rest. 
 
As with all my computers i offer a 'no questions asked'  refund within the first 15 days and a replace/repair warranty for the first 30. 
 
I am very easy to deal with, and i encourage you to ask me any questions you have about this or about laptops in general, this is my favorite topic.

title: Lenovo X1 Carbon Ultrabook Notebook - i7 / 8gb RAM / 256 SSD *EXTRAS*
description:
I write code for a living.   
 
What I am offering for sale is a total computing solution rather than a mere computer.  I bought it as a graduation present to myself for $1200 a couple years ago it was incredibly fast then and even faster now. 
 
The lenovo x1 carbon is pretty much the perfect amount of machine.  It masterfully blends power and performance while not cutting many corners.  Here are the raw specs, they kind of tell most of the story: 
 
Lenovo X1 Carbon, weighs 2 lbs 15 oz (see picture) 
 
Intel i5 2.5ghz multi core processor Hyper-Threading Technology, Intel Turbo Boost Technology 2.0 3mb cache, integrated memory controller 
 
8GB 1333 MHz PC3-10600 Ram 
 
120 GB Solid State Disk Drive 
 
Intel HD Graphics 4000 
 
Full size spill-resistant backlit keyboard 
 
Buttonless touchpad (like a macbook pro) 
 
Bluetooth 4.0, Ethernet, Fast Ethernet, Gigabit Ethernet 
 
Mini DisplayPort, USB 2.0, USB 3.0, headphone/microphone combo jack 
 
Fingerprint Scanner 
 
and all this is encased in a durable and impossibly light carbon fiber, magnesium-aluminum alloy frame. 
 
This machine cost $1500 in 2012 and it's easy to see why. 
 
 
If i had any complaints about this machine then it was merely  too few output ports.  Fret not, I got you covered, remember when I said total computing solution? 
 
So I am including with this machine - A docking station/port replicator that will send outputs to three different displays (that's a lotta desktop) as well as add an additional. 
 
When you plug this dock into the lenovo you will instantly add the following ports to the Carbon X1 
 
2 x USB 3.0 -- 1 provides always-on mobile device charging 
2 x USB 2.0 
1 x DVI-D 
1x Gigabit Ethernet 
1x Stereo/Mic Combo Port 
 
So in other words, you can leave a wireless mouse, wireless keyboard, a larger external display, a printer, and an external DVD drive plugged in to the stationary dock, and when you get home, plug the dock into your carbon and your home office springs to life.   
 
It's a pretty damn cool setup.  My price may seem high, but there's a reason for that.  I've done all the work for you, and am including several accessories.  this is ready to go. 
 
THIS WILL ALSO COME WITH A FULLY ACTIVATED COPY OF MS OFFICE 2016 PROFESSIONAL PLUS & PHOTOSHOP CS6 PREINSTALLED ON THE COMPUTER.

title: Dean Splittail Trans Red w OHSC
description:
Cash price is firm--open to TRADE OFFERS ONLY. 
 
The guitar is in excellent condition with little more than a couple pick swirls. The hard case is dying a slow death. Luckily the case did exactly what it should do--keep the guitar in pristine shape in the event of impact. There are 3 big dings in the case but the latches and hinges still work as they should to continue protecting/transporting the guitar. I'm essentially selling the guitar for $500 and throwing in the hard case for free. 
 
Better pics coming soon. 
 
Body Type: Split-tail  
Body Wood: Mahogany  
Scale Length: 24-3/4" 
Neck Joint: Set  
Neck Wood: Mahogany 
Fretboard: Rosewood  
Inlays: Pearl block  
Neck Shape: v  
Frets: 22  
Nut Width: 1-11/16"  
Fretboard Radius: 16"  
Bridge: Tune-o-matic-style  
Pickup Bridge: Dean USA Timecapsule 
Pickup Neck: Dean USA Timecapsule  
Controls: 1-vol 1-tone  
Tuners: Grover  
Pickup selector: 3 way  
Finish: gloss Trans Red 
 
Dean intended these to be the Zakk Wylde model (and you can see him using one, complete with Dean logo, on several Youtube videos) but Gibson had a legal claim and made them withdraw. So Dean removed any trace of Zakk's name and trademark finishes and sent them out as a standard model. This guitar is pleasantly light but puts out tone like crazy. It comes in the original form-fitting hard case. These were originally MSRP'd at over a $1k. 
 
Cash price is firm--open to TRADE OFFERS ONLY (absolutely no Squier or Epiphones, no MIM Fenders, no "player" MIJ Fenders, no broken/repaired guitars), may consider all-tube amps (no hybrid tube/SS, no ValveKings, no Crate), will also consider studio mics/gear, road gear, or newer Apple iMac 27" desktop or MacBook Pro Intel w Retina (newer processor chipsets only).

This laptop received a new battery, case, and keyboard as well as mainboard (because of faulty GPU switching) by Apple in March of 2015; total cost of this work was nearly the same as my asking price. 
 
Working Apple 85w Magsafe 2 adapter is included.

title: 2011 Apple MacBook Pro- Great Condition
description:
This MacBook (2.3 gHz/ 4GB / i5) is in great condition as you will see in the pictures. Runs really fast and I had a new battery installed at the apple store less than a year ago (cost me $150). I have never had issues with it. The Operating system is Mavericks. I have restored the laptop to factory settings so less work for its lucky new owner! 
 
There is a hairline fracture on the screen. It started as a little crack from my ring, but grew slightly larger. It is not at all noticeable when you are using the laptop and it can be replaced at home for under $25. The laptop comes in its original box with it's charger.  
 
All in all, great value for the price! Would be a great first laptop for someone looking for ease of use. 
 
I am asking for $375. I require that you pick it up in person. I will not ship it under any circumstances.

title: Macbook Pro Mid-2012 15" Retina
description:
I'm selling my MBP. It's served me well over the years. Why am I selling such a pristine work horse? I recently upgraded to a 13" model. Here's some of the finer points this Alan Turing dream machine... 
 
Tech Specs 
Processor: 2.6 GHz Intel Core i7  (SO MUCH POWA!!) 
Memory: 8 GB 1600 MHz DDR3 (VROOOM) 
Storage: 256 GB SSD (Access all your... pictures, or movies... with unlimited speed) 
Display: 15.4-inch (2800x1800) 
Graphics: Nvidia GeForce GT 650M 1024 MB 
Graphics: Intel HD Graphics 4000 MB 
 
Serial Number: c02j4geqdkq1 
 
This is a developer's dream. Just look at all the preinstalled stickers! Various vintage start up stickers including Rumgr and OpenBrew! Plus, you'll look super techie with JS flair, Backbone, Bocoup, Twitter's Bower, Mandrill, npm and more. Show up to the office looking like the "Ninja Rockstar" developer you are. Don't have a dev job yet? Show up to the interview with a Skinny Venti Soy Latte and this beast of a laptop and you're sure to be hired. Trust, it's worked in the past. 
 
I've kept the laptop in tip top shape. We've been to several Yoga classes, spin sessions and juice bars together. Yes, those are furniture coasters on the bottom of the laptop so it wouldn't get scratched as you slide it around your desk. They don't sell those coasters at the Apple Store, so you'll probably be approached by several Apple Fanboys asking "Where did you get those genius backside scratch protectors from". I reply "These old things? Oh they're just some iDots", walk away and secretly laugh to myself as I picture them going to the Apple Store and asking a "genius" for iDots... But I digress. 
 
I still have the original box, charger, the page turning warranty information booklet and more. I just got the laptop back from Apple Care where they completely replaced the motherboard and battery connector. It's basically a whole new brain! A computer lobotomy, if you will. You will... 
 
Please, use the Craigslist Reply button at the top of the page to contact me for more information. I'd be happy to give you my cell if you'd like to call and ask questions about this laptop, D&D strategy, Steely Danzig or whatever else (I don't like just posting my cell phone on Craigslist because that usually ends with untold amounts of spammers, tindr profiles, or solicitations to sell my car or this laptop - trust me I don't need help selling this laptop).

title: 17" Apple MacBook Pro ~ Logic ~ Final Cut ~ Photoshop
description:
Buy my MacBook Pro on Christmas Eve or Christmas Day. I can meet up either day.  Call or Text me at 
  
 
 
For Sale: 17" MacBook Pro Unibody  
 
I am selling my decked out 17 inch MacBook Pro.  
 
It is pretty much as loaded up as you can get.  
 
This MacBook Pro has been completely wiped and everything reinstalled fresh.  
 
 
 
Hardware: 
 
It has the 17" High-Res, Anti-Glare Display 
 
My Macbook Pro has a 500GB SSD and a 1TB HDD Installed (no disk drive, HDD is installed in disk drive area. That's a total of 1.5TB storage space.  
 
16GB RAM DDR3 1333Mhz in this MacBook Pro 17" 
 
My 17" MacBook Pro is in EXCELLENT condition. There are some minor scratches on the aluminum casing but nothing bad.  
 
This MacBook Pro runs like a BEAST! It is super fast and can run any of the heavy duty programs no problem.  
 
The battery is good and lasts for several hours while the MacBook Pro is unplugged. The cycle count is only 327!! 
 
This MacBook Pro has the backlit keyboard so you can use it in the dark. 
 
There is an Intel HD Graphics 3000 with 512MB onboard inside this MacBook Pro.  
 
Software: 
 
My 17 inch Macbook Pro laptop has Mac OS X 10.11.6 El Capitan Installed. (It is eligible for a free upgrade to Mac OS Sierra but I have not installed it.  
 
It has Microsoft Office Installed (Microsoft Word, Microsoft Excel, Microsoft Powerpoint0 
 
It has Adobe Photoshop Installed, as well as Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Audition, Adobe InDesign, and Adobe Premier Pro 
 
It has Adobe Acrobat X Pro installed as well. 
 
Logic. Yup that's right it has Apple Logic (music production software). 
 
It also has Apple Final Cut Pro Installed (Video Production Software). 
 
You will be hard pressed to find a better 17" MacBook Pro. This great Apple laptop computer is a steal of a deal at only $2500. If you had to buy this Macbook Pro new and add the upgrades and additional software it would have cost you over $6000.  
 
I am only selling it because I have recently purchased the new MacBook Pro and don't have a need for 2 laptops.  
 
I have cared for this MacBook Pro like it was my child. It is in great shape, runs perfectly and will continue to be a workhorse for years to come.  
 
Serious buyers only. I understand that this is one of the most expensive MacBook Pro models on Craigslist but it is also one of the most decked out computers you can buy. This is a great machine for someone who produces music or video. It would also be a great machine for a graphic designer. The 17" high res anti glare screen makes it great for editing.  
 
Local Buyers Only. Cash Only. No Trades.  
 
I am located in Downtown Mesa. There are several coffee shops nearby that we can meet at to do the deal.  
 
If you have any questions or want to take it for a test drive please call or text Justin at 
  
 Do not email, I will not respond to any emails due to scammers.
